data.name: HelpPage.ArchivingApps.Paragraph1
data.value: Archiving an application changes it into read-only mode and sets its status to decommissioned. Users will not be able to make changes to an archived application.

data.name: HelpPage.ArchivingApps.Paragraph2
data.value: To archive an application, first navigate to the page of the application you wish to archive. Then, click the settings button located at the top right of the page to navigate to the settings page of that application. Scroll to the bottom of the settings page and click the archive button under the other actions section. Confirm your decision in the popup that appears.

data.name: HelpPage.ArchivingApps.Paragraph3
data.value: You may follow the same steps to unarchive an application.

data.name: HelpPage.ArchiveDelRecoverApps.Paragraph1
data.value: Currently, only admins can archive, delete, and recover applications.

data.name: HelpPage.DelApps.Paragraph1
data.value: Deleting an application will make the application inaccessible to all non-admin users. Admin users will still be able to view the application in the application recovery page.

data.name: HelpPage.FavAndSubApps.Paragraph1
data.value: To favourite or subscribe to an application, first navigate to the page of your application of interest.

data.name: HelpPage.FavAndSubApps.Paragraph2
data.value: To favourite an application, click on the star icon button at the top right of the application’s page. Favouriting an application adds the application to your favourites list in the side bar. It also automatically subscribes you to the application, which means you will be receiving update and reminder notifications on changes made to the application by other users. Clicking on the star icon once again would unfavourite the application and it would no longer show up in your favourites list. However, you would still be subscribed to the application. If you are subscribed to an application, the subscribe button, located next to the star icon button, would have a checkmark appear in its left area. To unsubscribe from an application, click on that button. The checkmark should disappear.

data.name: HelpPage.&&operator.Paragraph1
data.value: The && operator is used to search for pages that contain multiple terms.

data.name: HelpPage.&&operator.Paragraph2
data.value: For instance, if you wish to find the security module of the MSAPR application, you can type in "MSAPR && security". This would look for pages that contain both the term “MSAPR” and “security”.

data.name: HelpPage.&&operator.Paragraph3
data.value: You may use the && operator in a search as many times as you wish.

data.name: HelpPage.DelApps.Paragraph2
data.value: To delete an application, first navigate to the page of the application you wish to delete. Then, click the settings button located at the top right of the page to navigate to the settings page of that application. Scroll to the bottom of the settings page of the application and click the delete button under the other actions section. Confirm your decision in the popup that appears. Note that applications deleted using the aforementioned steps can still be recovered.

data.name: HelpPage.DelApps.Paragraph3
data.value: To permanently delete an application, take the following additional steps. Note that applications will not be able to be recovered after you carry out these steps. Go to your side bar and click on the recover applications option in the admin panel submenu. The click would direct you to the application recovery page. Search for your application in the table displayed. Click on the delete option in the action column of the table.

data.name: HelpPage.EmailNotifs.Paragraph1
data.value: You would immediately get an email whenever an announcement has been sent to you by an admin. Reminders are sent to you by email at 5:00 AM 3 days in advance of the update due date. Each Friday, an email digest, which contains a summary of all notifications received that week (including announcements, reminders and updates) is sent to you through email. Note that emails will not be sent on weeks where there are no notifications.

data.name: HelpPage.EmailNotifs.Paragraph2
data.value: You can choose to change the frequency of receiving email digests, as well as the day of the week you wish to receive it. You can also choose to stop receiving email notifications entirely.

data.name: HelpPage.EmailNotifs.Paragraph3
data.value: To customize email notifications settings, go to the settings page and switch to the notifications tab. Use the customization options under the email notifications section.

data.name: HelpPage.InAppNotifs.Paragraph1
data.value: In app notifications can be viewed by clicking the bell icon located in the right area of the top bar. A red dot would appear next to the bell icon if there are unread notifications. Clicking on the bell icon opens a dropdown with two tabs, alerts and updates. The alerts tab contains announcements and reminders while the updates tab contains updates.

data.name: HelpPage.InAppNotifs.Paragraph2
data.value: If you receive a notification when you are logged in, a pop-up will appear at the top right corner of the screen containing that notification.

data.name: HelpPage.InAppNotifs.Paragraph3
data.value: If you receive notifications while you are logged off, announcements and reminders you missed will appear as pop-ups when you first log back into the app. You can also click on the bell icon to check for all notifications you received during your time away.

data.name: HelpPage.InAppNotifs.Paragraph4
data.value: You can choose to stop receiving pop-up notifications for updates and reminders. To do so, navigate to the settings page and switch to the notifications tab. Use the customization options under the in-app pop-up notifications section.

data.name: HelpPage.InAppNotifs.Paragraph5
data.value: You cannot turn off pop-up notifications for announcements.

data.name: HelpPage.Notifications.Paragraph1
data.value: There are three types of notifications in total: announcements, reminders, and updates.

data.name: HelpPage.Notifications.Paragraph2
data.value: Announcements are short messages created by admins. Admins can choose which users to send an announcement to. Reminders inform you of upcoming scheduled updates for applications you favourited 3 days in advance of the update due date. Updates inform you when changes are made to module fields of applications you favorited, except when such changes are made by you.

data.name: HelpPage.Notifications.Paragraph3
data.value: There are two ways you can view notifications, from within the ATM app, or from the email inbox associated with your ATM account.

data.name: HelpPage.QuickSearch.Paragraph1
data.value: The quick search is located in the right area of the top bar. Clicking on it opens a pop-up that allows you to quickly search for something in ATM and navigate to the page containing your search terms. You can use application names, module names, module fields and module field values as your search terms.

data.name: HelpPage.QuickSearch.Paragraph2
data.value: You may use the operators && and || to combine search teams to make more advanced searches.

data.name: HelpPage.RecoverApps.Paragraph1
data.value: To recover a deleted application, go to your side bar and click on the recover applications option in the admin panel submenu. The click would direct you to the application recovery page. Search for your application in the table displayed. Click on the restore option in the action column of the table.

data.name: HelpPage.RecoverApps.Paragraph2
data.value: Note that you will not be able to recover permanently deleted applications and they will not show up in the table.

data.name: HelpPage.||operator.Paragraph1
data.value: The || operator is used to search for pages that contain one or more of multiple search terms.

data.name: HelpPage.||operator.Paragraph2
data.value: For instance, if you wish to find all applications that contain either the security or identification module, you can type in "security || identification".

data.name: HelpPage.||operator.Paragraph3
data.value: You may use the || operator in a search as many times as you wish.
